metadata.name: Washed Trees Fluor #9
metadata.description:
‚ÄúOur Love had heard that an immortal language never could die, although silent, it still slept somewhere amongst the birches, lost ever since the day when we went weeping from beneath the angel-guarded gates of Eden.‚Äù

In Inner Purple Forest ‚ÄúWashed Trees Fluor‚Äù, rainbow bubbles-shaped form sprouts like fungi from a birch log. 

With its disconcerting conjunction of the natural and man-made, this still life recalls the way that nutrients in dead plant material are reclaimed by other living things as part of nature‚Äôs cycle of decay and rebirth.

No matter how long or hard we might gaze upon these ghostly images remain the same, they are not allowed to gather too much dust, they do not lose their bloom.

metadata.name: Pobbles #65
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

‚Ä¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
‚Ä¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
‚Ä¢ Alternative titles considered include Peggles‚Ñ¢, Plops‚Ñ¢, Blobbies‚Ñ¢, Floofs‚Ñ¢, Flintstones‚Ñ¢, Lardies‚Ñ¢, Plumps‚Ñ¢, Fats‚Ñ¢ and Wet-Ones‚Ñ¢. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
‚Ä¢ They work well with toddlers.

üñ®Ô∏è Collectors minting at the first auction tier receive a hand-crafted riso print of their pobble. Color variation between the file and the print will apply. üñ®Ô∏è

metadata.description:
Witness hundreds of small geometric objects gather under one roof to create a cosmic rain!

Ever since I was a child, I have always been good with geometric objects. I used to draw objects such as cubes, cylinders and prisms on paper for hours. As if I'm getting lost in every line between those geometric objects! In this way, every detail of geometry in my daily life and in my other existing life attracts my attention.

Recently, I have been doing research on colors and color palettes, it is really impressive how thousands of color mixtures affect each other and the psychology of living things!

metadata.name: Plottable Thousands #117
metadata.description:
'Thousands' explores the packing of recursive circles and golden angle spirals distributing various particles on a A4 canvas.

A SVG file can be exported (right click save) to plot the piece physically.

You can enjoy the digital version that simulate ink effects and optional, thanks to the utility token decoupling, get a physical one: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors ‚Äì as long as NFT is owned at request time.

Code: https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-thousands

@greweb ‚Äì 2022 ‚Äì tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM ‚Äì CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Plant remains #24
metadata.description:
Black and white photography, from film to digital to constrained and dithered greys palette 2500x2500 pixels. 

Layered tonalities from six film scans piling randomly.

Pics made in the south of France : the mountains above Grasse for the thistles and around the lake of St Cassien when it was very low, showing the old stumps usually hidden under the water.

Those stumps are remains of the nature before the lake was created in the 60's.
Sometimes when the lake is very low i take some time to shoot what's hidden under the surface.

The thistles are all dead in the pics (autumn), in some you can see the seeds preparing a new start for the following season.

Rare types of colors can show up in the last translucent layer to honor old analog photography : Cyanotype (1/5), Vandyke (1/10), Virage (1/10)

Some results can be strange but that's the point of random exploration. Feel free to try variations before minting ;-)

Click on the opened image to generate a download icon.

If you want to print the image please upscale without interpolation to preserve the dithering.

By Palancus (@Palancus)

Previous collectors have a reserved mint for a few days after release.

Big thanks to @PureSpider for his useful template.

metadata.name: CA Class 4 #4
metadata.description:
Class 4 cellular automatons produce a combination of randomness and order.  All of the class 4 rules‚Äô patterns are more complex than their Class 3 cousins.  Class 4 structures emerge, move around, and interact with one another before petering out or evolving.  Whereas class 3 automatons are analogous to irrational numbers, class 4 automata behave more like living organisms.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

Props and attribution to Stephen Wolfram, Johnny Von Neumann and Nils Aall Barricelli

objkt.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #110

metadata.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #110
metadata.description:
Experimental generative collection that merges analog photography, AI, generative text, and algorithmic coding, by digging down into the essence and building blocks of the different artistic communication channels. 

This work engages with all aforementioned mediums in a joint manner, guided by a random process. It starts with a collection of analog photographs, shot on film and scanned that were later used as a training dataset in Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) training. This way, A.I. learns the main characteristics of film photography. In particular, it mimics its recognizable grain. Another type of pixel grain is added with the use of code and pixel shifting as well as digital manipulation. Finally, the last type of ‚Äúgrain‚Äù appears with the use of generative text where a different kind of A.I. was given a short description of the project and instructed to imagine the rest of the story. The fragmented and void of meaning parts of generative text are added to the images as one of the possible traits.
